---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/base.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms and Conditions"
  description="Terms and conditions, privacy policy, and legal information for Significa."
>
  <article class="legal">
    <div class="legal-inner">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="legal-header">
        <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
      </header>

      <!-- Dispute Information -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Dispute information</h2>
        <p>In case of dispute, the consumer may resort to an Alternative Dispute Resolution Entity:</p>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>CICAP – Tribunal Arbitral de Consumo</strong></p>
          <p>
            Rua Damião de Góis, 31, Loja 6,<br />
            4050-225, Porto
          </p>
          <p>
            +351 22 550 83 49 / +351 22 502 97<br />
            <a href="mailto:cicap@cicap.pt">cicap@cicap.pt</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            More information at: <a href="https://www.consumidor.gov.pt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >https://www.consumidor.gov.pt</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Privacy Policy -->
      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

        <h3>Introduction</h3>
        <p>
          At Significa (Significa, Lda.) we are committed to fair practices that protect and respect your privacy. We want you
          to know we don't store any personal information from our visitors.
        </p>

        <h3>Laws, Regulations and Supervisory Authority.</h3>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of Portugal without regard to its conflict of laws provision. You consent
          to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in connection with any action or dispute arising between the parties under
          or in connection with this Privacy Policy.
        </p>

        <h4>The laws that govern personal data in Portugal are:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            REGULATION (EU) 2016/679 OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural
            persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing
            Directive 95/46/EC (General Data Protection Regulation) ("GDPR").
          </li>
          <li>Lei n.º 67/98 de 26 de Outubro, LEI DA PROTECÇÃO DE DADOS PESSOAIS.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The independent authority that upholds information rights in the public interest in Portugal is the Comissão Nacional
          de Protecção de Dados (the "CNPD"). Further information can be found at: <a
            href="https://www.cnpd.pt"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.cnpd.pt</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3>Who is Significa?</h3>
        <div class="company-info">
          <p><strong>Significa, Lda.</strong></p>
          <p>Registered address: Casa do Soto, 4540-226 Burgo, Arouca, Portugal</p>
          <p>Company VAT Number: PT513884556</p>
          <p>
            Email: <a href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3>Information we may collect from you.</h3>
        <p>
          We do not collect any personal information from you. We are privacy-friendly. Our cloud service providers may collect
          anonymous information about our users.
        </p>

        <h3>Information you give us.</h3>
        <p>You may give us information about you with your consent, including, but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>By filling in a form or sending us an email.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This information may be personal or related to your business or employment history. You may give us information for
          legal reasons, such as to enter into a contract with us, when you are buying services from us, or when you are taking
          a job at Significa.
        </p>

        <h3>Information we collect about you.</h3>
        <p>
          We collect data on accesses to our site for purely statistical purposes, counting the number and duration of accesses.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not use cookies and no personal data is collected, processed or stored/archived, and users remain completely
          anonymous.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you visit our website we may automatically collect information about the type of device you use. What parts of our
          website you click on and how long you look at our website.
        </p>

        <h3>Why does Significa collect personal information?</h3>
        <p>We don't collect any personal information about Significa's website visitors. We do collect form submissions.</p>

        <h3>What legal basis does Significa have for processing my information?</h3>
        <p>
          Significa only processes your information if you submit one of the contact forms. By doing so, you are giving us
          permission to process and store your submitted information.
        </p>

        <h3>How long will you keep my personal information?</h3>
        <p>
          The information you submitted through one of our contact forms will be stored until we decide to erase it from our
          databases or if you request us to do so. To do so, please contact: <a href="mailto:hello@significa.co"
            >hello@significa.co</a
          >
        </p>

        <h3>Where we store your personal data</h3>
        <p>
          The information you submitted through any of our contact forms is stored and/or processed at one of the following
          third-party service providers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Notion</li>
          <li>Slack</li>
          <li>AWS</li>
          <li>Vercel</li>
          <li>PostHog</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Should you wish to request your information to be deleted from any of the above sources, please contact: <a
            href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3>Managing privacy and security of Client data</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Significa Client Data:</strong> Significa securely stores all Client-related data, including contracts, signatures,
          and contact information, within its internal knowledge management system (e.g., Notion). Access to this data is strictly
          limited to personnel who require it for specific, authorised purposes. Significa does not use Client data for any purposes
          beyond those necessary to fulfil contractual obligations, such as invoicing and the delivery of agreed-upon services.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the course of delivering services, Significa may utilise various tools for communication, messaging, and data
          storage. These tools may rely on third-party service providers; however, Client data is only used as required to
          support the agreed services. Significa remains committed to maintaining the confidentiality and security of Client
          data at all times.
        </p>
        <p>
          In order to deliver its services, Significa relies on a number of third-party service providers ("Sub-Processors").
          These tools are used to facilitate communication, messaging, and data storage. While Significa uses these
          Sub-Processors to support its operations, Client data is handled strictly in accordance with its intended purpose,
          limited to fulfilling contractual obligations and providing agreed-upon services. Significa ensures that all
          Sub-Processors adhere to industry-standard practices for data security and privacy. A list of the Sub-Processors used
          by Significa is provided below:
        </p>

        <div class="sub-processors">
          <div class="sub-processor">
            <h4>Notion</h4>
            <p>Company name: Notion Labs, Inc.</p>
            <p>Registered Address: 2300 Harrison Street, San Francisco, CA 94110</p>
            <p>Country of Registration: United States</p>
            <p>Significa's purpose of use: Knowledge management system</p>
          </div>

          <div class="sub-processor">
            <h4>Slack</h4>
            <p>Company name: Slack Technologies, LLC</p>
            <p>Registered Address: 50 Fremont Street, San Francisco, CA 94105</p>
            <p>Country of Registration: United States</p>
            <p>Significa's purpose of use: Communication and instant messaging</p>
          </div>

          <div class="sub-processor">
            <h4>Google Workspace</h4>
            <p>Company name: Google LLC</p>
            <p>Registered Address: 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, California, 94043</p>
            <p>Country of Registration: United States</p>
            <p>Significa's purpose of use: Email, file storage and sharing, virtual meeting</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          <strong>End Customer Data:</strong> End Customer data is processed and managed exclusively through the applications ("Products")
          developed by Significa for its Clients. In instances where these Products handle End Customer data, the responsibility for
          the management, control, and ownership of such data resides solely with the Client. Significa does not possess or claim
          ownership over End Customer data; its role is limited to developing and maintaining the tools necessary to support the storage
          and handling of this data on behalf of the Client.
        </p>
        <p>
          At all times, the Client retains full authority and discretion over End Customer data, including the ability to revoke
          Significa's access, as this data is hosted entirely on platforms, servers, or services owned or controlled by the
          Client (e.g., the Client's cloud provider). While Significa offers guidance and adheres to best practices to assist
          the Client in ensuring the security of End Customer data, ultimately Significa does not own these hosting
          environments.
        </p>

        <h3>Is the information collected through the service secure?</h3>
        <p>
          We take precautions to protect the security of your information. We have physical, electronic, and managerial
          procedures to help safeguard, prevent unauthorised access, maintain data security, and correctly use your information.
          However, neither people nor security systems are foolproof, including encryption systems. In addition, people can
          commit intentional crimes, make mistakes or fail to follow policies. Therefore, while we use reasonable efforts to
          protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
        </p>

        <h3>Who might Significa share your information with?</h3>
        <p>We won't share any of your information unless we must comply with a legal obligation.</p>

        <h3>Your Rights</h3>
        <p>
          Significa will respect your legal rights to your data. Below are the rights that you have under the law, and what
          Significa does to protect those rights:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to be informed:</strong> Significa is publishing this Legal Statement to keep you informed as to what
            we do with your information. We strive to be transparent about how we use your data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to access:</strong> You have the right to access your information. Please contact Significa at <a
              href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a
            >, if you wish to access the information Significa holds about you.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to rectification:</strong> If the information Significa holds about you is inaccurate or not complete,
            you have the right to ask us to rectify it. Please contact Significa if you need us to rectify your information: <a
              href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to erasure:</strong> This is sometimes called 'the right to be forgotten'. If you want Significa to
            erase all your data and we do not have a legal reason to continue to process and hold it, please contact Significa at:
            <a href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to object:</strong> You have the right to object to Significa processing your data even if it is based
            on our legitimate interests, the exercise of official authority, direct marketing (including data aggregation), and processing
            for the purposeless of statistics. If you wish to object please contact Significa at: <a
              href="mailto:hello@significa.co">hello@significa.co</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The right to complain to a Supervisory Authority:</strong> You have the right to complain to the CNPD if you feel
            that Significa has not responded to your requests to solve a problem. You can find their contact details here:
            <a href="https://www.cnpd.pt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.cnpd.pt</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Cookies</h3>
        <p>We do not use cookies.</p>

        <h3>Links to Other Websites</h3>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to and from the websites of our partners, suppliers and other third parties. We have no
          control over the content or links displayed on these sites. If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note
          that these websites may have their own privacy policies and that we do not accept any responsibility or liability for
          any such policies. Please check these policies, where available, before you submit any personal data to these
          websites.
        </p>

        <h3>Children</h3>
        <p>
          Significa does not believe its website or marketing content is appealing to children, nor is it directed at children
          under 13. Significa does not work with Clients, nor employ anybody, under the age of 18.
        </p>

        <h3>Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p>
          Significa has the discretion to update this privacy policy at any time. Any such changes will be updated here and,
          where appropriate, notified to you in writing. We advise you to check back frequently to check for any reviews or
          changes.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Legal Document
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .legal {
    padding: 8rem var(--gutter) 4rem;
  }

  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 50rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Header
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
  }

  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Sections
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .legal-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-section:first-of-type h2 {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section h4 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-section p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.15em;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    transition: opacity var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out);
  }

  .legal-section a:hover {
    opacity: 0.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal-section strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
  }

  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Contact Block
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .contact-block {
    background: var(--color-surface-alt);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .contact-block p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Company Info
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .company-info {
    background: var(--color-surface-alt);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .company-info p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .company-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* --------------------------------------------------------
       Sub-processors
       -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .sub-processors {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .sub-processor {
    background: var(--color-surface-alt);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }

  .sub-processor h4 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .sub-processor p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .sub-processor p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
